<div class="page-sustainability pt-nav">

  {%- comment -%} Hero {%- endcomment -%}
  <div style="position:relative;height:40vh;min-height:280px;overflow:hidden;">
    <img
      src="{{ 'sustainability-hero.jpg' | asset_url }}"
      alt="Sustainability"
      style="width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;"
    >
    <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:rgba(0,0,0,0.45);display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;justify-content:center;text-align:center;padding:2rem;">
      <h1 style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:clamp(2.5rem,6vw,4.5rem);color:#fff;margin-bottom:1rem;letter-spacing:0.05em;">Sustainability</h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.1rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);max-width:500px;">Committed to responsible luxury</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  {%- comment -%} Intro {%- endcomment -%}
  <section style="padding:5rem 0;background:#fff;">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;">
      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:2rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;text-align:center;">The Real Story</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);text-align:center;line-height:1.8;font-size:1.05rem;margin-bottom:3.5rem;">
        Sustainability isn't a marketing campaign for us — it's how we've operated since 1989. We own and run our own tannery in Ambato, Ecuador, which means we control every step of the process and answer for every decision we make.
      </p>

      {%- comment -%} Four Pillars {%- endcomment -%}
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1.5rem;margin-bottom:3.5rem;">

        <div style="background:#f5f0ea;padding:2rem;">
          <svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" style="color:var(--color-accent);margin-bottom:1rem;"><path d="M17 8C8 10 5.9 16.17 3.82 19.82A2 2 0 0 0 5.5 22.5c1.5 0 4-2 4-2s-1 3 1 3 5-3 5-3 0 2 2 2 4-4 4-4c-1-2-3-4-3-4z"/><path d="M5.5 12.5c3-3 5-5 7.5-5"/></svg>
          <h3 style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:1.4rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">100% Natural Bovine Leather</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.8;font-size:0.95rem;">
            Every hide we use is natural bovine leather, tanned and cut at our own facility in Ambato. No synthetic materials, no shortcuts. The leather is a by-product of the food industry — the animal is never raised for leather alone.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="background:#f5f0ea;padding:2rem;">
          <svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" style="color:var(--color-accent);margin-bottom:1rem;"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
          <h3 style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:1.4rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Regulated & Monitored</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.8;font-size:0.95rem;">
            Our tannery operates under strict oversight from Ecuadorian environmental authorities. We maintain our own water treatment plant to ensure all wastewater meets the required standards before it leaves our facility.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="background:#f5f0ea;padding:2rem;">
          <svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" style="color:var(--color-accent);margin-bottom:1rem;"><polyline points="23 4 23 10 17 10"/><polyline points="1 20 1 14 7 14"/><path d="M3.51 9a9 9 0 0 1 14.85-3.36L23 10M1 14l4.64 4.36A9 9 0 0 0 20.49 15"/></svg>
          <h3 style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:1.4rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Zero Leather Waste</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.8;font-size:0.95rem;">
            Every leather scrap from our production is reused. Nothing goes to waste. Offcuts become smaller goods and components, keeping our material usage as efficient as possible from the first cut to the final product.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="background:#f5f0ea;padding:2rem;">
          <svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" style="color:var(--color-accent);margin-bottom:1rem;"><path d="M20.84 4.61a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 0L12 5.67l-1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 7.78l1.06 1.06L12 21.23l7.78-7.78 1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0 0-7.78z"/></svg>
          <h3 style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:1.4rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Local Community</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.8;font-size:0.95rem;">
            Every person who works in our tannery comes from the same mountain community in Ambato. This is a family business built on local labor — not outsourced, not faceless. The same hands, the same families, for over 35 years.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>

      {%- comment -%} Leather vs Plastic callout {%- endcomment -%}
      <div style="padding:2rem 2rem 2rem 2.5rem;border-left:4px solid var(--color-accent);background:#f9f6f2;">
        <h3 style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:1.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">The Plastic Problem Nobody Talks About</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);margin-bottom:1rem;line-height:1.8;">
          Many brands promote "vegan leather" as an eco-friendly alternative. In reality, most of it is PU — a plastic-based material that sheds microplastics, doesn't biodegrade, and ends up in landfills within a few years. Real leather, made responsibly, biodegrades naturally and lasts decades.
        </p>
        <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.8;margin:0;">
          At DIAZ, we believe the most sustainable choice is a product built to last — made from a natural material, by real people, in a facility we own and stand behind.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</div>

<style>
@media (max-width: 767px) {
  .page-sustainability [style*="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr"] {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
  }
}
</style>

